<subSubSection id="5CC4BFDEB2D024764891AE7B3DFC54AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="6D70CDE1606D0B3934C71F0C53B6045D" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="464B224A485DAFF8ABA69035DEEBC287" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, this species ranges 11-13 mm in total length and 2.5-3 mm in maximum width. During the current census it has been observed mainly at night under artificial lights, however on one occasion it was found during daytime feeding on flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="B619BDD2362E614A7921A46E49D07A4B" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Oleaceae" genus="Ligustrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ligustrum sinense" order="Oleales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sinense">
<emphasis id="36CE795817979FC8BDE4A9018D7925DD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ligustrum sinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In nearby Hong Kong, larvae have been documented to bore into wood of 
<taxonomicName id="2CB39997CFC7661EC4792CED3723769C" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lauraceae" genus="Cinnamomum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cinnamomum camphora" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="camphora">
<emphasis id="05EC8CA372CD7F468160685D9E337845" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Cinnamomum camphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="888AB6CB87C8C00A0D58B9A69F2A1FFE" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Citrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Citrus" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7934D94684E899C6BF2680DECFE7D9D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Citrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., and 
<taxonomicName id="579ACAF100D51E171D30802A2848EC81" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" genus="Melia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Melia azedarach" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="azedarach">
<emphasis id="E50DD6E9724B83C90E463384A590CF7C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Melia azedarach</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4A558E4E48FBC9E2401E94AB46970985" author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="E9BECBF2FC01625B33D5E0C453FAAA0D" author="Liu, L-R" journalOrPublisher="Entomological Knowledge" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="100 - 102" refId="B94" refString="Liu, L-R, 1992. Bionomics of Ceresium sinicum ornaticolle Pic and its control. Entomological Knowledge 28 (2): 100 - 102" title="Bionomics of Ceresium sinicum ornaticolle Pic and its control." volume="28" year="1992">Liu (1992)</bibRefCitation>
reported them as serious pests of 
<taxonomicName id="88722489149ABEEDF39C75ADFE5248ED" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lythraceae" genus="Punica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Punica granatum" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="granatum">
<emphasis id="6CF293600D2621D59A465DE9F8EC21FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Punica granatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Sichuan, but also more generally of 
<taxonomicName id="5102E6227A593E86C4E6A8F73AD9067C" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="Malus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Malus domestica" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="domestica">
<emphasis id="A195BC2B733E1A2013C810DE0923E2AC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Malus domestica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E53A53B50517398F2BBB36061C4AE1E6" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="Pyrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pyrus" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E53B94098D76114EBD9AF2F6B58804D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Pyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and 
<taxonomicName id="90ECF142192AC58D421D0A2B30F0C6C4" class="Insecta" family="Ricinidae" genus="Ricinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ricinus communis" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis id="0E67354D82E9807288973995E5FAD25F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ricinus communis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
